<subSubSection id="C31915D0FF9D99611DF5F95C60C5F89E" pageId="8" pageNumber="175" type="key">
<keyStep id="30F75EFEFF9D99611DF5F95C60C4F8A3" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">
<paragraph id="8BBC465BFF9D99611DF5F95C60C5F964" blockId="8.[151,1437,1684,1853]" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">
<keyLead id="30F2E56EFF9D99611DF5F95C60C5F964" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">
1. Elytra with a distinct, complete, black midelytral fascia (
<figureCitation id="13385ADEFF9D99611E6EF95C661DF908" box="[780,837,1684,1706]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1550]" captionTargetId="figure-102@4.[151,1436,345,1560]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Tarsobaenus letourneauae, n. sp. (paratypes): 1—dorsal habitus; 2—head; 3—male, ventral abdomen; 4—female, ventral abdomen; 5—elytral plica; 6—lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6557095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6557095/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); metepisternum testaceous (
<figureCitation id="13385ADEFF9D99611901F95C61C7F908" box="[1123,1183,1684,1706]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1550]" captionTargetId="figure-102@4.[151,1436,345,1560]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Tarsobaenus letourneauae, n. sp. (paratypes): 1—dorsal habitus; 2—head; 3—male, ventral abdomen; 4—female, ventral abdomen; 5—elytral plica; 6—lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6557095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6557095/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); pronotum with a central black vitta (
<figureCitation id="13385ADEFF9D99611C36F97964D4F965" box="[340,396,1713,1735]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1550]" captionTargetId="figure-102@4.[151,1436,345,1560]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Tarsobaenus letourneauae, n. sp. (paratypes): 1—dorsal habitus; 2—head; 3—male, ventral abdomen; 4—female, ventral abdomen; 5—elytral plica; 6—lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6557095" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6557095/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
)................................................................ 
<taxonomicName id="4C033DD8FF9D996119FCF97960C5F964" authorityName="Leavengood &amp; Pinkerton &amp; Rifkind" authorityYear="2022" box="[1182,1437,1713,1734]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarsobaenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="letourneauae">
<emphasis id="B9779A49FF9D996119FCF97960C5F964" box="[1182,1437,1713,1734]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">Tarsobaenus letourneauae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC465BFF9D99611DF5F90760C4F8A3" blockId="8.[151,1437,1684,1853]" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">
<keyLead id="30F2E56EFF9D99611DF5F90760C4F8A3" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">
1’. Elytra with or without a fascia (when present, fascia located anteriorly) (
<figureCitation id="13385ADEFF9D99611EFEF90766B9F946" box="[924,993,1743,1765]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1411,1435]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1386]" captionTargetId="figure-26@6.[151,1436,181,1387]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Tarsobaenus piper, n. sp. (holotype, paratype): 7—holotype, dorsal habitus; 8—head; 9—paratype, dorsal habitus; 10—elytral plica; 11—lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6557097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6557097/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">Figs. 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13385ADEFF9D99611E89F907615EF947" box="[1003,1030,1743,1765]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–16" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1473,1497]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,237,1443]" captionTargetId="figure-48@8.[151,1436,237,1449]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 12–16. Tarsobaenus hansoni, n. sp. (holotype, paratype): 12—holotype, dorsal habitus; 13—head; 14—paratype, dorsal habitus; 15—elytral plica; 16—lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6557101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6557101/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">12</figureCitation>
); metepisternum black (
<figureCitation id="13385ADEFF9D9961198CF9076065F946" box="[1262,1341,1743,1765]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1411,1435]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1386]" captionTargetId="figure-26@6.[151,1436,181,1387]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Tarsobaenus piper, n. sp. (holotype, paratype): 7—holotype, dorsal habitus; 8—head; 9—paratype, dorsal habitus; 10—elytral plica; 11—lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6557097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6557097/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">Figs. 11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13385ADEFF9D99611825F9076039F947" box="[1351,1377,1743,1765]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–16" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1473,1497]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,237,1443]" captionTargetId="figure-48@8.[151,1436,237,1449]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 12–16. Tarsobaenus hansoni, n. sp. (holotype, paratype): 12—holotype, dorsal habitus; 13—head; 14—paratype, dorsal habitus; 15—elytral plica; 16—lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6557101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6557101/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">16</figureCitation>
); pronotum either immaculate (
<figureCitation id="13385ADEFF9D99611CBDF924677BF8A3" box="[479,547,1772,1794]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1411,1435]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1386]" captionTargetId="figure-26@6.[151,1436,181,1387]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Tarsobaenus piper, n. sp. (holotype, paratype): 7—holotype, dorsal habitus; 8—head; 9—paratype, dorsal habitus; 10—elytral plica; 11—lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6557097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6557097/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">Figs. 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13385ADEFF9D99611F4FF9246732F8A0" box="[557,618,1772,1794]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–16" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1473,1497]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,237,1443]" captionTargetId="figure-48@8.[151,1436,237,1449]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 12–16. Tarsobaenus hansoni, n. sp. (holotype, paratype): 12—holotype, dorsal habitus; 13—head; 14—paratype, dorsal habitus; 15—elytral plica; 16—lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6557101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6557101/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">12, 14</figureCitation>
) or with black lateral vittae (
<figureCitation id="13385ADEFF9D99611EE2F92466E2F8A0" box="[896,954,1772,1794]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1411,1435]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1386]" captionTargetId="figure-26@6.[151,1436,181,1387]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Tarsobaenus piper, n. sp. (holotype, paratype): 7—holotype, dorsal habitus; 8—head; 9—paratype, dorsal habitus; 10—elytral plica; 11—lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6557097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6557097/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
)...................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30F75EFEFF9D99611DF5F8C160C5F89E" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">
<paragraph id="8BBC465BFF9D99611DF5F8C160C4F8BC" blockId="8.[151,1437,1684,1853]" box="[151,1436,1801,1823]" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">
<keyLead id="30F2E56EFF9D99611DF5F8C160C4F8BC" box="[151,1436,1801,1823]" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">
2. Basal half of elytra black (except for anterior margin, which is narrowly testaceous) (
<figureCitation id="13385ADEFF9D99611971F8C16101F8BD" box="[1043,1113,1801,1823]" captionStart="FIGURES 12–16" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1473,1497]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,237,1443]" captionTargetId="figure-48@8.[151,1436,237,1449]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 12–16. Tarsobaenus hansoni, n. sp. (holotype, paratype): 12—holotype, dorsal habitus; 13—head; 14—paratype, dorsal habitus; 15—elytral plica; 16—lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6557101" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6557101/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
)......... 
<taxonomicName id="4C033DD8FF9D996119B2F8C160C4F8BC" authorityName="Leavengood &amp; Pinkerton &amp; Rifkind" authorityYear="2022" box="[1232,1436,1801,1822]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarsobaenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hansoni">
<emphasis id="B9779A49FF9D996119B2F8C160C4F8BC" box="[1232,1436,1801,1822]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">Tarsobaenus hansoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBC465BFF9D99611DF5F8EF60C5F89E" blockId="8.[151,1437,1684,1853]" box="[151,1437,1831,1853]" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">
<keyLead id="30F2E56EFF9D99611DF5F8EF60C5F89E" box="[151,1437,1831,1853]" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">
2’. Elytra entirely orangish (
<figureCitation id="13385ADEFF9D99611CB0F8EF6753F89E" box="[466,523,1831,1853]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1411,1435]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1386]" captionTargetId="figure-26@6.[151,1436,181,1387]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Tarsobaenus piper, n. sp. (holotype, paratype): 7—holotype, dorsal habitus; 8—head; 9—paratype, dorsal habitus; 10—elytral plica; 11—lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6557097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6557097/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) or with epipleural margin narrowly black (
<figureCitation id="13385ADEFF9D99611ED2F8EF66B1F89F" box="[944,1001,1831,1853]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–11" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1411,1435]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1386]" captionTargetId="figure-26@6.[151,1436,181,1387]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7–11. Tarsobaenus piper, n. sp. (holotype, paratype): 7—holotype, dorsal habitus; 8—head; 9—paratype, dorsal habitus; 10—elytral plica; 11—lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6557097" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6557097/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
).................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C033DD8FF9D99611988F8EF60C5F89E" authorityName="Leavengood &amp; Pinkerton &amp; Rifkind" authorityYear="2022" box="[1258,1437,1831,1852]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarsobaenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piper">
<emphasis id="B9779A49FF9D99611988F8EF60C5F89E" box="[1258,1437,1831,1852]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="175">Tarsobaenus piper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
